  "prompt": "What universities does Inteliquent recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Inteliquent, a telecommunications company, typically recruits new graduates from universities with strong technical and engineering programs. While specific universities may vary based on their recruitment strategies and partnerships, they often seek graduates who have pursued majors such as:\n\n- Computer Science\n- Electrical Engineering\n- Computer Engineering\n- Information Technology\n- Telecommunications\n\nAdditionally, they might also consider graduates from business, finance, or other related fields depending on the roles they are looking to fill. It\u2019s always a good idea for interested candidates to directly check Inteliquent's careers page or contact their recruitment team for the most current information regarding their hiring practices and preferred universities.",
